RACE.RACE_TEXT: THISTLEDOWN RACE 1 1M Dirt CR: 92. Starter Optional Claiming Purse 20000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE STARTED FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OF $5,000 OR LESS IN 2022 - 2023 OR CLAIMING PRICE $8,000. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 123 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over Since August 5 Allowed 2 lbs. Such A Race Since July 5 Allowed 4 lbs. Claiming Price $8,000 (Claiming Races For $5,000 Or Less Not Considered In Weight Allowances) (Ohio Registered Foals Preferred).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: TOE TAPPIN LUKE never far back, rallied outside rivals five wide under mild right handed urging and got up in the final strides. ROYAL DRAGOON unhurried early, closed rapidly four wide and just missed. MY BROTHER CAM stalked the pace along the inside into the stretch, lacked room inside the furlong marker, shifted out two wide and finished with good courage. PATIO PARTY bore in at the start bumping LEXATOGA, set the pace until deep stretch then was outfinished. FLIPPING FISH pressed the pace two wide, moved closer nearing the quarter pole, battled into the stretch then leveled off late. LAUDA SPEED moved up three wide before a half, had speed into the stretch then came up empty. LEXATOGA was bumped at the start and outrun. VENETIAN DREAM was through after a half.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: THISTLEDOWN RACE 4 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 50. Maiden Special Weight Purse 33900. FOR REGISTERED OHIO FOALS MAIDENS, FILLIES TWO YEARS OLD. Weight, 118 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SALTMAKESHERSWEET made the lead soon after the start, set all the pace, drifted inward striking WOMAN'S DREAM just past the furlong marker and edged clear late under mild urging. BIG FACTS reluctant to load, prompted the pace three wide and finished second best. SNOWBIRD passed tiring rivals. BLIZZARD was no threat. MS. DEBBIE ALAN bore in at the start and was never close. HONEY BEE GOOD settled mid pack, stumbled over a fallen foe just past the furlong marker and unseated her rider. WOMAN'S DREAM vied for the lead along the rail into the stretch, drew closer inside the winner before the eighth pole, was struck by that one causing her to stumble, unseated her rider then fell over the fallen rider. THE STEWARDS POSTED THE INQUIRY SIGN AND AFTER REVIEW DISQUALIFIED SALTMAKESHERSWEET FOR INTERFERENCE IN MID STRETCH AND PLACED HER FIFTH.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: THISTLEDOWN RACE 5 1M Dirt CR: 82. Claiming Purse 12600. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON TWO RACES SINCE MARCH 5. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 123 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over Since August 5 Allowed 2 lbs. Such A Race Since July 5 Allowed 4 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000 (Ohio Registered Foals Preferred).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: IT'S FATE had speed from the start along the rail, slipped through to make the lead at the seven sixteenths pole, set the balance of the pace, drifted out to the five path despite strong right handed urging through the stretch and was all out to prevail. LAZARUS PROJECT saved ground through the far turn, loomed boldly outside the winner, was carried out to the six path and just missed. NOBLE BEHAVIOR set the early pace off the rail, kept on into the stretch, drifted out to the middle of the racetrack and lost ground. ALGORIX well placed, faded in the stretch. DEBDURITE pressed the pace three wide for five and one half furlongs and weakened late. ROSAS WAY had no impact. THE RIDER OF LAZARUS PROJECT LODGED A CLAIM OF FOUL AGAINST THE RIDER OF THE WINNER FOR ALLEGED INTERFERENCE IN THE STRETCH. AFTER REVIEW THE STEWARDS UPHELD THE ORIGINAL ORDER OF FINISH.
